last_episode_to_air.name: What You Leave Behind (2)
last_episode_to_air.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko leads, what he hopes will be, a final all-out assault on Cardassia Prime. Kira and Garak mount a suicidal assault on the Cardassian headquarters occupied by the Dominion, who in turn kill innocent women and children village by village in retaliation for the Resistance's attacks.

name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine
overview: At Deep Space Nine, a space station located next to a wormhole in the vicinity of the liberated planet of Bajor, Commander Sisko and crew welcome alien visitors, root out evildoers and solve all types of unexpected problems that come their way.

episodes.name: Deep Space Nine: A Bold Beginning
episodes.overview: A bonus included on the Season 1 DVD box set release, this feature includes interviews with Michael Piller (1 October 1992), Rick Berman (7 June 2002), and Avery Brooks (4 November 1992) on the making of Star Trek: Deep Space Nine. The subsection Designing Deep Space Nine featured interviews about the creation from early drafts to the built model with Herman Zimmerman (7 June 2002), Michael Okuda (9 October 2002), Rick Sternbach (7 October 2002), and Ricardo Delgado (19 April 1993). It also features a few behind the scenes filming shots from several episodes of the first season.

episodes.name: Crew Dossier: Kira Nerys

episodes.name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine: Behind the Scenes
episodes.overview: As Star Trek: Deep Space Nine airs it's pilot episode, Paramount airs this 50 minute documentary as a way to spark excitement about the new show. It includes interviews from the cast and crew and contains lots of sneak peaks into the show's first season. This TV special originally aired on January 4, 1993 in the UK but wasn't released for home media until July 20, 1994 in the U.S.

guest_stars.character: Capt. Jean-Luc Picard / Locutus of Borg
guest_stars.name: Patrick Stewart

episodes.name: Emissary (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46379.1.  Commander Benjamin Sisko and a new crew of Starfleet and Bajoran officers take command of an abandoned Cardassian space station and make an incredible discovery that will change the galaxy and Sisko's future.

guest_stars.character: Capt. Jean-Luc Picard / Locutus of Borg
guest_stars.name: Patrick Stewart

episodes.name: Emissary (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46379.1. A new crew is assigned to a former Cardassian space station: Deep Space Nine. It is a joint Federation/Bajoran force, with Commander Sisko in charge, but his life is dramatically changed when he is declared the Emissary to the Prophets by a Bajoran priest.

episodes.name: Past Prologue
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  Kira finds her loyalties divided when a Bajoran extremist wanted by the Cardassians comes to the station with questionable intentions.

episodes.name: A Man Alone
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46421.5.  When the return of a man Odo sent to prison years earlier leads to his murder aboard the station, Odo becomes the prime suspect and a target for harassment.

episodes.name: Babel
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46423.7.  A deadly virus created by the Bajorans 18 years earlier inadvertently breaks loose aboard the station, and prompts a race against the clock to find a cure.

episodes.name: Captive Pursuit
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  When O'Brien befriends the station's first visitor from the Gamma Quadrant, he learns that the mysterious alien is on the run from determined pursuers.

episodes.name: Q-Less
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46531.2.  Vash arrives from the Gamma Quadrant as Q plagues the station and an unknown force threatens to destroy it.

episodes.name: Dax
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46910.1.  Jadzia Dax is charged with a murder that her symbiont's previous host Curzon allegedly committed. Now an extradition hearing may decide whether Jadzia can be held responsible for the actions of a previous life.

episodes.name: The Passenger
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  A dangerous killer dies in an apparent accident, but the security officer providing his transport to prison believes the criminal's consciousness may have yet survived.

episodes.name: Move Along Home
episodes.overview: The Wadi from the Gamma Quadrant are to make first contact and decide to visit DS9. When they catch Quark cheating they let him off by playing a special game.

episodes.name: The Nagus
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  Grand Nagus Zek, the leader of Ferengi society, comes to DS9 to oversee the introduction of a Ferengi business presence in the Gamma Quadrant and announce Quark as his successor.

episodes.name: Vortex
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  A wanted man from the Gamma Quadrant with questionable motives reveals to Odo stories about other "Changelings," which may hold clues to Odo's mysterious origin.

episodes.name: Battle Lines
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  Sisko, Kira, and Bashir take Kai Opaka through the wormhole for a brief excursion in the Gamma Quadrant. But when they crash-land on a desolate planet, they find a divided, warring penal colony where no one ever dies.

episodes.name: The Storyteller
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46729.1.  When O'Brien and Bashir beam down to a Bajoran village, the community selects O'Brien as their next Sirah - expecting him to save them from a menacing entity.

episodes.name: Progress
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46844.3.  Kira finds herself in a difficult moral situation when her job demands she force an adamant Bajoran man from his home in the name of progress.

episodes.name: If Wishes Were Horses
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46853.2.  The DS9 crew's own imaginations cause mysterious beings with unknown intentions to appear on the station.

episodes.name: The Forsaken
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46925.1.  Odo and Lwaxanna Troi come to a mutual understanding when a computer malfunction causes them to become trapped in a turbolift.

episodes.name: Dramatis Personae
episodes.overview: Stardate: 46922.3.  An alien "telepathic matrix" causes the DS9 crew to re-enact an ancient power struggle, leading Kira to attempt mutiny and overthrow Sisko.

episodes.name: Duet
episodes.overview: A Cardassian suffering from Kalla-Nohra, a disease that indicates he served in a labor camp, visits DS9. Kira is determined to convict him as a war criminal.

episodes.name: In the Hands of the Prophets
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown.  The Federation and Bajoran people of DS9 fall into conflict when a Bajoran religious extremist comes to the station and challenges the secular teachings of Keiko O'Brien's school.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The Provisional Government of Bajor invites Starfleet to help them rebuild after the Cardassian Occupation. Commander Benjamin Sisko is selected to take command of their space station, formerly known as Terok Nor that is then designated by Starfleet as Deep Space 9. As part of the agreement between the Federation and Bajor, Starfleet will help them to become a member of the Federation.

episodes.name: The Homecoming (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Word that a previously thought dead Bajoran resistance legend is still alive sends Kira and Chief O'Brien to Cardassia IV to rescue him; meanwhile "The Circle", a sect of the Bajoran provisional government that is intent on wiping out alien influence, is sneaking into power.

episodes.name: The Circle (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kira spends time with Vedek Bareil on Bajor just as "The Circle" begins arming themselves from a mysterious source.

episodes.name: The Siege (3)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. As a "Circle"-led Bajoran military tries to occupy the station, a skeleton crew led by Sisko fight to reveal "The Circle's" big secret before they are forced to evacuate themselves. Meanwhile, Kira and Dax lead a mission to reveal the truth about "The Circle" on Bajor.

episodes.name: Invasive Procedures
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47182.1. A jealous Trill, who had waited his entire life to receive a symbiont but never had, decides to steal one. . . Dax's!

episodes.name: Cardassians
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47177.2. Political heat rises on the station as Bajorans enter the station with orphaned Cardassians they have adopted.

episodes.name: Melora
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47229.1. A new arrival to the station with a special gravity-based disability appeals to Bashir's heart; meanwhile an old associate of Quark's comes to the station to kill the barkeep.

episodes.name: Rules of Acquisition
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A female Ferengi, posing as a male to be available to participate in business (a rule STRICTLY forbidden by the Ferengi government), falls for Quark during very important negotiations between the Ferengi and a Gamma Quadrant race.

episodes.name: Necessary Evil
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47282.5. Odo relives some terrible and tragic memories of a past investigation when he was the constable on Cardassian-occupied Deep Space Nine, then named Terok Nor.

episodes.name: Second Sight
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47329.4. While noted scientist Gideon Seyetik is preparing for an ambitious project, re-igniting a star, Sisko is intrigued by a woman who keeps disappearing.

episodes.name: Sanctuary
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47391.2. A race that has been conquered twice over, one of the conquerors being the mysterious Dominion, comes to the station seeking aid and a new home.

episodes.name: Rivals
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark meets his match when a new rival opens a casino opposite Quark's Bar on the Promenade; meanwhile the station is suffering issues of high improbability.

episodes.name: The Alternate
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47391.7. Odo and Dr. Mora Pol, Odo's 'father', discover a life form similar to Odo on a Gamma Quadrant planet.

episodes.name: Armageddon Game
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47529.4. Chief O'Brien, who still doesn't like the good Doctor Bashir, must rely on him when the two are stranded on a planet and O'Brien is infected with a deadly, fast moving disease.

episodes.name: Whispers
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47581.2. Chief O'Brien's world is turned upside down when for no reason whatsoever he is being ignored by his family and friends and is being closed out of every essential job on the station.

episodes.name: Paradise
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47573.1. Sisko and Chief O'Brien discover a colony that lives without technology.

episodes.name: Shadowplay
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47603.3. Odo and Dax investigate the mysterious disappearance of people from a village. Kira tries to keep a close eye on Quark, while Vedek Bareil unexpectedly visits.

episodes.name: Playing God
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A Trill named Arjin comes to DS9 to learn what it is to be a Trill with a symbiont but finds his teacher, Dax, to be less than he expected.

episodes.name: Profit and Loss
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A Cardassian woman, who was once a former flame of Quark's, visits the station under dubious circumstances.

episodes.name: Blood Oath
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Three legendary Klingons come to DS9 to see if Jadzia Dax will participate in a Blood Oath they made with Jadzia's previous host Curzon.

episodes.name: The Maquis (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The destruction of a Cardassian ship leads Sisko, Dukat, and Sisko's old friend Cal Hudson to the fact that there is an unofficial war between the Maquis and the Cardassians.

episodes.name: The Maquis (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko tries to resolve the Maquis crisis by preventing a war, freeing Gul Dukat and offering the defected Hudson the chance to return.

episodes.name: The Wire
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Bashir fights to save Garak's life when a malfunctioning  Cardassian brain implant threatens to kill him.

episodes.name: Crossover
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47879.2. Kira and Bashir find themselves in an alternate universe.

episodes.name: The Collaborator
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Vedek Bareil is accused of having betrayed his people to the Cardassians during the occupation, and Major Kira is desperate to prove his innocence.

episodes.name: Tribunal
episodes.overview: Stardate: 47944.2. Chief O'Brien goes through the horrific Cardassian judicial system when he is charged for an unknown crime.

episodes.name: The Jem'Hadar
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko and Quark and a strange telepathic woman are arrested by Jem'Hadar, soldiers of the Dominion.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In their second year together, the crew of Deep Space 9 face problems that will affect the galaxy forever. A Bajoran extremist group attempts to force the Federation out of the Bajoran system. The Cardassians are secretly supplying them with weapons, hoping to return to reclaim the planet and hold the Bajoran wormhole for the Cardassian Union. However, the greatest enemy of all is lurking beyond it.

episodes.name: The Search (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48213.1. Instead of waiting for the Jem'Hadar to attack, Sisko wants to try a different approach. He wants to take a new class starship to try to find the Founders.

episodes.name: The Search (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48213.1. Odo has found his home and is introduced. Meanwhile Sisko finds out peace talks between the Dominion and the Federation have already started.

episodes.name: The House of Quark
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark tries to boost his reputation by taking credit for the accidental death of a Klingon in his bar, but lands himself in the middle of a Klingon political struggle.

episodes.name: Equilibrium
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The Trill homeworld is the setting, as Sisko and Bashir take Jadzia home for treatment when she begins experiencing hallucinations after playing a tune she can't recall.

episodes.name: Second Skin
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kira finds herself on Cardassia as a Cardassian. She is told she is called Iliana Ghemor and was a Cardassian spy.

episodes.name: The Abandoned
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Odo tries to bond with an alien child Quark finds in a load of salvage, while Sisko tries to break his son's relationship with a 20 year old Dabo girl.

episodes.name: Civil Defense
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The station goes into lockdown and the crew is endangered when an old Cardassian security program is accidentally activated.

episodes.name: Meridian
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48423.2. Dax falls in love with one of the residents of a multi-dimensional planet, while on DS9 an alien requests a holosuite program of Kira from Quark.

episodes.name: Defiant
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48467.3. The DS9 crew welcomes a visit from William Riker of the Enterprise, but the lieutenant’s hidden agenda leads to a tense standoff deep in Cardassian space.

episodes.name: Fascination
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. As Lwaxanna Troi visits the station for a Bajoran festival, the crew is stricken with intense romantic attractions to one another.

episodes.name: Past Tense (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48481.2. Sisko, Bashir and Dax are accidentally sent to San Francisco in the 21st century due to a transporter malfunction, and must figure out how to get back without changing the time line.

episodes.name: Past Tense (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48481.2. Sisko is forced to take the place of a key historical figure on Earth in 2024 in order to preserve the timeline.

episodes.name: Life Support
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48498.4. Dr. Bashir must use extraordinary measures to prolong Vedek Bareil's life long enough to allow Bareil to complete sensitive peace negotiations between the Bajorans and the Cardassians.

episodes.name: Heart of Stone
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48521.5. After chasing a fugitive into a cave, Kira gets stuck and is slowly encapsulated by a growing crystal stone while Odo tries to figure out how to free her.

episodes.name: Destiny
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48543.2. Sisko faces a conflict between his Starfleet duties and his role as the Bajoran Emissary when an ancient Bajoran prophecy predicts that a joint Federation-Cardassian project will lead to the destruction of the wormhole.

episodes.name: Prophet Motive
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Grand Nagus Zek is acting bizarre by giving away money and rewriting the Rules of Acquisition. Quark attempts to get the old Nagus back.

episodes.name: Visionary
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. While a Romulan delegation tries to get information about the Dominion, O'Brien gets visions of unpleasant things that are about to happen in the future.

episodes.name: Distant Voices
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. After being attacked in the infirmary, Dr. Bashir has a dual mystery on his hands: what has happened to the station while he was out and why is he aging so rapidly now?

episodes.name: Through the Looking Glass
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko is kidnapped to impersonate his deceased, mirror universe self to gain Jennifer Sisko's loyalty in the Rebel Alliance.

episodes.name: Improbable Cause (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. After an attempt is made on Garak's life, Odo conducts the investigation on who tried to murder the Cardassian tailor - and why.

episodes.name: The Die Is Cast (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Now rejoined with his former mentor, Garak is ordered to interrogate Odo about the secrets of his people, while the joined Romulan/Cardassian attack fleet moves towards the Founders' home world on a mission of destruction.

episodes.name: Explorers
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko rebuilds an ancient Bajoran space vessel from the blueprints, and he and Jake take the ship on a trip, attempting to prove that the ancient Bajorans went beyond their solar system without warp drive.

episodes.name: Family Business
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark and Rom return to the Ferengi home world because their mother has broken the law - by wearing clothes and earning profits, forbidden for women in Ferengi society.

episodes.name: Shakaar
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. News arrives that Kai Winn has also become Bajor's political leader. She asks Kira to negotiate with an old resistance friend about returning soil reclamators.

episodes.name: Facets
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dax asks the crew to join her Zhian'tara ritual. The memories of her former hosts will take over their bodies. Nog is preparing for Starfleet Academy.

episodes.name: The Adversary
episodes.overview: Stardate: 48959.1. The Defiant is off to show the Federation's presence to the new Tzenkethi government. While underway the ship malfunctions and Bashir is suspected of sabotage.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Season 3 of Deep Space Nine marks a turning point for the series, as it introduces the USS Defiant, a powerful starship that allows the crew to explore the Gamma Quadrant and face the threat of the Dominion, a vast and ruthless empire ruled by the shape-shifting Founders.

episodes.name: The Way of the Warrior (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49011.4.  When the Klingons bring a task force to DS9, Captain Sisko sends for Starfleet's lone Klingon officer, Worf, to uncover the mysterious intentions of their presence.

episodes.name: The Way of the Warrior (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49011.4. Sisko becomes uncomfortable when the Klingons station a task force to help defend against the Dominion. Worf is summoned to find out their true intentions.

episodes.name: The Visitor
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Melanie, an aspiring writer, wants to know why Jake Sisko stopped writing at 40. Jake tells how his father died in an accident and then suddenly reappeared.

episodes.name: Hippocratic Oath
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49066.5. Bashir is asked to help a group of renegade Jem'Hadar break their addiction to ketracel white. Meanwhile Worf is dissatisfied with the way Odo runs security.

episodes.name: Indiscretion
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kira and Gul Dukat go after the lost prison ship Ravinok. Dukat has a secret. Meanwhile Kasidy Yates tries to find work near Bajor, leaving Sisko uncomfortable.

episodes.name: Rejoined
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49195.5. Lenara Kahn, the new host of the wife of Dax's former host Torias, comes to the station. While they're not allowed to renew their relation, there's still a spark.

episodes.name: Starship Down
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49263.5. A damaged Defiant must play a dangerous game of cat-and-mouse with two Jem'hadar ships inside a gas giant.

episodes.name: Little Green Men
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark and Rom take Nog to Earth and Starfleet Academy, but a malfunction with the ship takes the crew back in time, to Roswell New Mexico in 1947.

episodes.name: The Sword of Kahless
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Worf, Dax and the Klingon Dahar master Kor set out to find an ancient lost relic: the Sword of Kahless.

episodes.name: Our Man Bashir
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When an transporter emergency turns the command crew into holosuite characters, Bashir's James Bond fantasy takes on a deadly reality.

episodes.name: Homefront (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49170.65. Sisko travels to Earth when a bombing at a Federation conference is determined to be the work of Changelings.

episodes.name: Paradise Lost (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When Starfleet institutes martial law to combat the Changeling Menace, Sisko begins to question if the Dominion is the real threat.

episodes.name: Crossfire
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. First Minister Shakaar visits the station, despite a threat of assassination. He falls in love with Kira much to Odo's dismay.

episodes.name: Return to Grace
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dukat returns, stripped of his prestige, to escort Kira to a Cardassian conference about the Dominion. But an attack by a Klingon raider may give Dukat a chance to redeem himself in the eyes of his government.

episodes.name: Sons of Mogh
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49556.2. Worf's brother Kurn asks him to perform a death rite to regain his lost honor. Meanwhile Kira and O'Brien investigate Klingon activity near the Bajoran border.

episodes.name: Bar Association
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Unfair working conditions and pay cuts cause Rom to organize a union of the employees of Quark's Bar. Meanwhile Worf still finds it hard to settle on the station.

episodes.name: Accession
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A man claiming to be the emissary comes through the wormhole. Sisko is happy to give up his position. Meanwhile Keiko returns and O'Brien stops spending time with Bashir.

episodes.name: Rules of Engagement
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49665.3. When Worf destroys a civilian shuttle during an engagement with the Klingons, an extradition hearing is held to see if he must face charges.

episodes.name: Hard Time
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. O'Brien tries to re-integrate to life on the station after serving 20 years in a virtual prison.

episodes.name: Shattered Mirror
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When the Mirror Universe counterpart of Sisko's deceased wife lures Jake to the other side, Sisko must follow and help the human resistance against the Alliance's forces.

episodes.name: The Muse
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A mysterious woman approaches Jake about his future as a writer. Odo promises to do whatever it takes to help Lwaxana Troi keep her baby over the father's wishes - even if it means marrying her himself.

episodes.name: For the Cause
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko must face betrayal when evidence surfaces that Kasidy is smuggling for the Maquis. Meanwhile Garak makes acquaintance with Ziyal.

episodes.name: To the Death
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49904.2. A renegade group of Jem'Hadar plunders Deep Space Nine. Sisko agrees to a combat operation with loyal Jem'Hadar to prevent the renegades completing a planetary gateway.

episodes.name: The Quickening
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Bashir tries to help a planet in the grips of a Dominion-engineered plague that guarantees a painful death.

episodes.name: Body Parts
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quarks hears on Ferenginar he is going to die. Rom convinces him to sell his remains. After an accident, Bashir has to move Keiko's baby to Kira's womb.

episodes.name: Broken Link
episodes.overview: Stardate: 49962.4. Odo is suddenly struck by illness. He is barely able to hold shape. Bashir and Odo see no other alternative then going to the Founders. Garak wants to come along.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: Season 4 of Deep Space Nine marks a major shift for the series, as it introduces a new conflict between the Federation and the Klingon Empire, sparked by the latter's distrust of the shape-shifting Founders. Worf, the former security chief of the USS Enterprise-D, joins the station's crew as Sisko's strategic operations officer, and faces challenges in his loyalty, honor, and family.

episodes.name: Apocalypse Rising
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. With the war between Klingons and Federation intensifying, Sisko must make a plan to expose Gowron as a changeling. Odo is still having trouble with becoming a solid.

episodes.name: The Ship
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50049.3. The crew find a crashed Jem’Hadar ship and work to repair it and capture it for the Federation, but are confronted by a Dominion force determined to recover the ship’s cargo.

episodes.name: Looking for par'Mach in All the Wrong Places
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. While Worf helps Quark to pursue his former wife Grilka, O'Brien and Kira grow uncomfortably close to each other.

episodes.name: Nor the Battle to the Strong
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Jake, reporting from the front lines, sees what war truly is.

episodes.name: The Assignment
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. An alien entity has possessed Keiko's body and is holding it hostage until O'Brien completes an assignment for it.

episodes.name: Trials and Tribble-ations
episodes.overview: Stardate: 4523.7. In this celebration of the 30th anniversary of The Original Series, the disgraced Klingon spy Darvin travels back in time to undo his century-old defeat by James Kirk. The DS9 crew must track him down and stop him, while blending in with the crew of the original Enterprise NCC-1701.

episodes.name: Let He Who Is Without Sin...
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. While vacationing on Risa, Worf and Dax meet a group of fundamentalist protesters who claim that the Federation has gone soft.

episodes.name: Things Past
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko, Dax, Odo and Garak find themselves in the past when the Cardassians controlled the station, and a crime that Odo investigated may be the key.

episodes.name: The Ascent
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When Odo and Quark crash land, they must put aside their differences to climb a mountain to signal for help. Jake and Nog try to be roommates, but their different styles clash.

episodes.name: Rapture
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. After a brain injury, Sisko begins experiencing powerful visions through time. He dives fully into the role of the Emissary, while becoming obsessed with finding a legendary Bajoran ruin.

episodes.name: The Darkness and the Light
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50416.2. A mysterious assassin begins wiping out all the members of Kira's old resistance cell.

episodes.name: The Begotten
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The discovery of an infant Changeling gives Odo a chance to put right the trauma of his own upbringing, while his “father” Dr. Mora insists on a more clinical approach.

episodes.name: For the Uniform
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50485.2. When the traitorous Eddington returns, Sisko will go to any lengths to capture him.

episodes.name: In Purgatory's Shadow (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A coded message from the Gamma Quadrant leads Garak to believe his mentor, Enabran Tain, is still alive. He and Worf seek him out, only to discover something much worse: a Dominion invasion fleet poised to attack the Alpha Quadrant.

episodes.name: By Inferno's Light (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50564.2. The station readies for a Dominion attack. Worf and Garak meet some unexpected friends in a Dominion Prison camp.

guest_stars.character: Dr. Lewis Zimmerman / EMH Mark I
guest_stars.name: Robert Picardo

episodes.name: Doctor Bashir, I Presume?
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Bashir is selected to be the model for the next-generation of Emergency Medical Hologram (EMH). But he balks when his parents are invited to the station to be interviewed by the EMH programmer, Dr. Zimmerman. There is a dark secret in his family that he's afraid that his parents will reveal.

episodes.name: A Simple Investigation
episodes.overview: Odo helps a woman hiding on the station from organized criminals, but quickly develops a personal interest in the case.

episodes.name: Business as Usual
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark must wrestle with his conscience when he becomes involved with arms merchants.

episodes.name: Ties of Blood and Water
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50712.2. When a Cardassian official that thinks of Kira as his daughter is dying, he agrees to reveal all he knows to her. But the experience dredges up Kira's memories of her own father's death.

episodes.name: Ferengi Love Songs
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark doesn't know whether to be panicked or overjoyed when he learns that his mother is the new lover of the Grand Nagus.

episodes.name: Soldiers of the Empire
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dax and Worf accompany Martok on his first command since being held by the Dominion. But the ship they are given hasn't seen victory in months and the crew is near mutinous.

episodes.name: Children of Time
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50814.2. The DS9 crew discovers a colony that, due to a time travel accident, turns out to be inhabited by the crew's own descendants.

episodes.name: Blaze of Glory
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko learns that the Maquis are planning a devastating attack on Cardassia, and must rely on the traitor Eddington to help him prevent it.

episodes.name: Empok Nor
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. While salvaging components from DS9's sister station, the crew run afoul of a "surprise" left behind by the Cardassians.

episodes.name: In the Cards
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50929.4. Jake has his heart set on a vintage Willie Mays baseball card as a present to cheer up his father, whose spirits are flagging from the ongoing conflict.

episodes.name: Call to Arms
episodes.overview: Stardate: 50975.2. Sisko decides to mine the wormhole to prevent further Dominion ships crossing into the Alpha Quadrant. This provokes an attack by the Dominion and the Cardassians, and a desperate last stand on Deep Space Nine.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: Season 5 of Deep Space Nine begins the Dominion War arc that will dominate the rest of the show. The Federation and its allies face a new enemy in the form of the Cardassian-Dominion alliance, which threatens to conquer the Alpha Quadrant.

episodes.name: A Time to Stand
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Borrowing a captured Jem'Hadar attack ship, Sisko and crew embark on a mission to destroy the hidden base where all of the ketracel-white is stored for the entire Alpha Quadrant.

episodes.name: Rocks and Shoals
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko and his crew crash on a barren world when their commandeered Jem'Hadar ship is shot down. They encounter Jem'Hadar who crashed there earlier, and have taken Nog and Garak hostage in exchange for medical aid for their Vorta overseer.

episodes.name: Sons and Daughters
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Serving with his recruit son aboard a Klingon vessel, Worf finds his relationship with his son strained. Meanwhile, strained relationships abound on DS9 between Major Kira and Gul Dukat.

episodes.name: Behind the Lines
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51145.3. After forming an attack plan on the Dominion, Sisko relinquishes command of the Defiant to Dax after accepting a promotion. On DS9, the resistance faces discovery when Odo links with another changeling.

episodes.name: Favor the Bold (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko mounts an attack to re-take DS9, while Rom faces charges as an enemy of the Dominion state.

episodes.name: Sacrifice of Angels (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The Federation attacks DS9 in hopes of keeping the mine field in the wormhole intact, while the Dominion waits entrance to the Alpha Quadrant from the other side.

episodes.name: You Are Cordially Invited
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51247.5. Suddenly desiring to wed within the week on DS9, Worf and Jadzia go through their own Klingon rituals: Worf on a four day bachelor party with the male members of the crew & Jadzia deals with her prospective mother-in-law, who totally opposes the idea of "an alien" marrying into her Klingon household.

episodes.name: Resurrection
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Major Kira takes a romantic interest in a Bajoran radical from the other universe who transports himself into her universe and onto DS9.

episodes.name: Statistical Probabilities
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A group of genetically engineered humans are brought to Dr. Bashir on DS9 in hopes of integrating them with the rest of the universe.

episodes.name: The Magnificent Ferengi
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. At the request of the Grand Nagus, Quark puts together a mission to rescue Quark's mother, who is in the hands of the Dominion.

episodes.name: Waltz
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51408.6. After being attacked by Cardassian forces, Sisko gets stranded with a very psychotic Gul Dukat, who was being transported to his trial. Meanwhile the crew of the Defiant races to rescue survivors.

episodes.name: Who Mourns for Morn?
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A former patron of Quark's bequeaths everything to him.

episodes.name: Far Beyond the Stars
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Captain Sisko has a full sensory vision of himself as an under-appreciated science fiction magazine writer in 1950s America.

episodes.name: One Little Ship
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51474.2. An attack by the Dominion on Sisko's ship endangers Dax and her crew aboard as she leads them into an anomaly that shrinks them to a very minute size. Unfortunately, they were being held stable by Sisko within a tractor beam, which was discontinued during the attack.

episodes.name: Honor Among Thieves
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Chief O'Brien goes undercover to infiltrate an Orion crime ring.

episodes.name: Change of Heart
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51597.2. Worf and Jadzia travel to the badlands to procure some information on the Dominion from a traitorous Cardassian. Bashir wants to engage in a holo-suite spy simulation, but O'Brien prefers to brush up on his tongo game after watching Jadzia lose to Quark.

episodes.name: Wrongs Darker Than Death or Night
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. After receiving some disturbing information from Gul Dukat, Major Kira seeks Sisko's approval as Emissary to travel back in time to find out the truth about her mother. Meanwhile, Chief O'Brien and Dr. Bashir discuss a holosuite program surrounding the Battle of the Alamo.

episodes.name: Inquisition
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Bashir's plans to attend a medical conference at a breezy resort are canceled when Starfleet Intelligence boards DS9, suspecting the doctor of treason.

episodes.name: In the Pale Moonlight
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51721.3. To save the Federation in a critical scheme, Sisko comes to realize that he must violate its fundamental principles to do so.

episodes.name: His Way
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Odo is schooled in the ways of romance by a holographic programmed lounge singer.

episodes.name: The Reckoning
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko runs afoul of Kai Winn when he removes a Bajoran artifact from an archaeological dig after he receives a vision from the Prophets.

episodes.name: Valiant
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51825.4. Jake and Nog's runabout comes under attack from the Jem'Hadar. They are rescued by the Valiant, a ship manned by Red Squad, a elite group of young Starfleet cadets.

episodes.name: Profit and Lace
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark's mother and the Grand Nagus show up on DS9, announcing a new amendment to the Bill of Opportunities he has instituted on the home planet of Ferenganar, and then follows up with the announcement, that, due to the new amendment, chaos has followed and he has been deposed.

episodes.name: Time's Orphan
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The Chief's daughter gets caught in a time displacement and when they get her back, she is considerably older.

episodes.name: The Sound of Her Voice
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51948.3. As the Defiant races to a shipwrecked officer who is days away, the crew keeps in contact with her. Meanwhile, Jake follows Quark's latest scheme for story research.

episodes.name: Tears of the Prophets
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When Sisko is picked to head up an attack on the Cardassian homeworld, the Prophets appear to him in a vision, warning him of impending doom if he leaves the station.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: Season 6 of Deep Space Nine marks the height of the Dominion War arc, as it depicts the Federation and its allies in a desperate struggle against the Cardassian-Dominion alliance, which has occupied Deep Space Nine and the Bajoran system.

episodes.name: Image in the Sand
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko, laying low on Earth since the wormhole's disappearance, receives a vision of an unfamiliar woman he believes is the key to regaining contact with the Prophets. Meanwhile, Kira faces the challenge of commanding Deep Space Nine and upholding the fragile alliance with the Romulans, and Worf must cope with the loss of Jadzia Dax.

episodes.name: Shadows and Symbols
episodes.overview: Stardate: 52152.6. Ezri Dax joins Sisko and his family on his quest for the Orb of the Emissary.  Jadzia's friends and family seek a glorious battle that will earn her place in Sto-vo-kor. Kira gambles the alliance with Romulans by blockading their weapons installation on Bajor's moon.

episodes.name: Afterimage
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Ezri Dax struggles to adjust to her new joined identity and her complicated relationships with Jadzia's friends. Meanwhile, Garak tries to deal with a severe bout of claustrophobia.

episodes.name: Take Me Out to the Holosuite
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A Vulcan captain challenges Sisko to a game of baseball.

episodes.name: Chrysalis
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Bashir’s genetically engineered friends return to the station, seeking his help in rousing one of them from her catatonic state.

episodes.name: Treachery, Faith, and the Great River
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A Vorta offers Odo valuable information on the Dominion in exchange for asylum. Meanwhile, Nog tries his Ferengi knowledge as he wheels and deals for a valuable piece of equipment for Chief O'Brien.

episodes.name: Once More Unto the Breach
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. An aged Kor requests an opportunity to die with honor as a warrior.

episodes.name: The Siege of AR-558
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Capt. Sisko and his away team volunteer to stay with a besieged unit at an isolate outpost.

episodes.name: Covenant
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kira is kidnapped and taken to Empok Nor by a member of a Pah'Wraith cult and discovers the group leader is Gul Dukat.

episodes.name: It's Only a Paper Moon
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Severely depressed at his serious war wound, Nog retreats into Vic Fontaine's holosuite program while the singer tries to help him.

episodes.name: Prodigal Daughter
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Ezri travels to her family home in search of Chief O'Brien who has discovered a murdered woman connected with the family and the Orion Syndicate.

episodes.name: The Emperor's New Cloak
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Quark and Rom have to rescue Grand Nagus Zek who is being held captive in the Alternate Universe.

episodes.name: Field of Fire
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. When a murder on the station stumps the crew, Ezri Dax reluctantly seeks help from the residual consciousness of the host she’d rather forget, the murderer Joran.

episodes.name: Chimera
episodes.overview: Stardate: 51474.2. A changeling arrives who, like Odo, says he’s grown up among humanoids with no knowledge of the Founders. He tries to convince Odo to leave humanoid society and live among changelings.

episodes.name: Badda-Bing, Badda-Bang
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. A hidden feature in Vic’s holosuite program causes the casino to be taken over by mobsters, and the DS9 crew plan a heist to take back their favorite hangout spot.

episodes.name: Inter Arma Enim Silent Leges
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Dr. Bashir is contacted again by Sloan of Section 31, who wants him to gather intel at an upcoming Romulan medical conference. Sisko agrees to send him, in order to learn more about Section 31 themselves.

episodes.name: Penumbra
episodes.overview: Stardate: 52576.2. When the ship Worf was serving on is attacked in battle and all search efforts are abandoned, Ezri takes a runabout in search of him against Sisko's orders. Meanwhile, Sisko proposes to Cassidy Yates.

episodes.name: 'Til Death Do Us Part
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. The Prophets disapprove of Sisko’s upcoming marriage, and he must make hard choices about his priorities. Ezri and Worf are captured by Dominion forces. Gul Dukat, disguised as a Bajoran, infiltrates DS9 and becomes close to Kai Winn.

episodes.name: Strange Bedfellows
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kai Winn gets unknowingly involved with Gul Dukat, disguised as a Bajoran. Tensions rise between Weyoun and Gul Damar as the Dominion gather to sign a peace treaty with the Breen. Ezri and Worf are captives on Cardassia.

episodes.name: The Changing Face of Evil
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. After the Breen attack Earth there are mixed emotions abound on DS9. Having revealed her secret regarding the Prophets to the disguised Dukat, Kai Winn turns her back on them, only to be convinced by Dukat to embrace the Pah Wraiths. On the home world of Cardassia, Legate Damar mounts a resistance to the Dominion.

episodes.name: When It Rains...
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Kira is sent to Cardassia to train their resistance. Dr. Bashir discovers that Odo has contracted the same disease threatening the Founders. Gowron arrives on DS9, announcing he’s taking control of the Klingon fleet from Martok.

episodes.name: Tacking Into the Wind
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Odo is affected by the disease threatening to eliminate his race more than he lets on. Kira has to deal with the Cardassian's dislike of her. Even though General Martok sees Chancellor Gowron's move as part of a political vendetta, he does nothing about it.

episodes.name: Extreme Measures
episodes.overview: Stardate: 52645.7. Dr. Bashir and Chief O'Brien go to extreme measures to try and track down a cure for Odo.

episodes.name: The Dogs of War
episodes.overview: Stardate: 52861.3. Odo begins his recovery from the deadly disease as Dr. Bashir informs him of Section 31's intentions of wiping out his race. A resistance mission goes bad for Kira and Garak and they end up hiding in the basement of the house that Garak grew up in, where they learned that Legate Damar has apparently become a casualty of war, despite him also hiding with them. Quark is chosen by the Grand Nagas as his successor upon his impending retirement to Risa.

episodes.name: What You Leave Behind (1)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko leads, what he hopes will be, a final all-out assault on Cardassia Prime. Kira and Garak mount a suicidal assault on the Cardassian headquarters occupied by the Dominion, who in turn kill innocent women and children village by village in retaliation for the Resistance's attacks.

episodes.name: What You Leave Behind (2)
episodes.overview: Stardate: Unknown. Sisko leads, what he hopes will be, a final all-out assault on Cardassia Prime. Kira and Garak mount a suicidal assault on the Cardassian headquarters occupied by the Dominion, who in turn kill innocent women and children village by village in retaliation for the Resistance's attacks.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: Season 7 of Deep Space Nine marks the end of the series, as it concludes the Dominion War arc and the saga of the characters and their relationships. The Federation and its allies face the final showdown with the Cardassian-Dominion alliance, which is aided by the Breen. Sisko and his crew must also deal with the threat of the pah-wraiths, the evil counterparts of the Prophets, who are unleashed by Kai Winn and Dukat.

tagline: At the edge of the Final Frontier, the Universe's greatest mystery is about to unfold.
